Forbes WelcomeCLOSE   More Options   Quote of the Day  The best life hack of all is to just put the work in and never give up. Bas Rutten, UFC Heavyweight Champion    Izhar Armony | AccompanyIzhar ArmonyGeneral Partner, CRVBIOGRAPHYCRV (Charles River Ventures)VlingoVRTUForbesVirtusa Corp.CaprizaVBProfilesLanyrdAngelListOtherMr. Izhar Armony serves as a General Partner of CRV. Mr. Armony joined Charles River Ventures in June 1997 and has built a portfolio of startups and exits since then. His investment interests mobile, SaaS, intellectual property, and energy. Mr. Armony served as a Partner at CRVelocity. He made many contributions to CRV, from recruiting and strategy development to sound council in building CRV infrastructure. He served at General Atlantic LLC, where he gained experience with enterprise software companies. He Co-Founded Onyx Interactive Ltd. and served as a Vice President of Marketing and Business Development. He was a Captain in the Israeli Army and an Officer for four years. He serves as a Director of Sense Labs, Inc., July Systems Inc., BusRadio, Mobeus, Optaros, Inc., Vlingo, Inc., Performable, Inc and iSkoot Technologies Inc. He serves as a Director of TerraPower LLC, GrabCAD OÜ, and Cybereason Inc. He has been an Independent Director of Virtusa Corp. since April 1, 2004. He serves as a Director of Qualcomm Connected Experiences, Inc. He serves as a Member of the Board of Directors of Xamarin Inc. He serves as a Director of Capriza, Inc. and 24M Technologies, Inc. He served as Director of RPX Corporation, from August 2008 to June 18, 2014. He served as a Director of Proficiency, Inc. and GlobalFoodExchange.com. He served as a Director of ThinkFire Services USA, Ltd., iBasis, Inc., Celarix, Inc., Aveksa, Inc., iPhrase Technologies, Inc, THINQ Learning Solutions, Inc., Guardent, Inc. and Yantra Corporation. Mr. Armony served as a Director of Gridstone Research, since March 2, 2006. He served as a Director of TalkingNets, Inc. Mr. Armony served as a Director of Perputo, Inc. since March 2006. He earned an M.B.A. from the Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania; an M.A. in International Studies from the University of Pennsylvania; and studies Cognitive Psychology from the University of Tel Aviv in Israel.The exec's best friend.The world's busiest CEOs, directors, and executives are
