Izhar Armony: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 26, 2017 5:29 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of CRV



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Izhar   Armony  General Partner , CRVAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 7 Board Members in 7 different organizations across 19 different industries.See Board Relationships54--
Background

		Mr. Izhar Armony serves as a General Partner at CRV. Mr. Armony joined Charles River Ventures in June 1997 and has built a portfolio of startups and exits since then. He was Partner at CRV since 1997. His investment interests include mobile, SaaS, intellectual property and energy.  Mr. Armony served as a Partner at CRVelocity. He made many contributions to CRV, from recruiting and strategy development to sound council in building CRV infrastructure. He served at General ... Atlantic LLC, where he gained experience with enterprise software companies. He Co-Founded Onyx Interactive Ltd. and served as a Vice President of Marketing and Business Development. He was a Captain in the Israeli Army and an Officer for four years. He serves as a Director of BusRadio, Mobeus and iSkoot Technologies Inc. He serves as a Director of Sense Labs, Inc., Airobotics Ltd, TerraPower LLC, Capriza, Inc and Cybereason Inc. He has been an Independent Director of Virtusa Corp. since April 1, 2004. He serves as a Director of 24M Technologies, Inc. He served as Director of Capriza, Inc. until September 30, 2016. He served as Director of RPX Corporation from August 2008 to June 18, 2014. He served as a Director of Qualcomm Connected Experiences, Inc., July Systems Inc., Optaros, Inc., Vlingo, Inc., GrabCAD OÜ, Xamarin Inc. and Performable, Inc. He served as a Director of Proficiency, Inc. and GlobalFoodExchange.com. He served as a Director of ThinkFire Services USA, Ltd., iBasis, Inc., Celarix, Inc., Aveksa, Inc., iPhrase Technologies, Inc, THINQ Learning Solutions, Inc., Guardent, Inc. and Yantra Corporation. Mr. Armony served as a Director of Gridstone Research, since March 2, 2006. He served as a Director of TalkingNets, Inc. Mr. Armony served as a Director of Perputo, Inc. since March 2006. He earned an M.B.A. from the Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania; an M.A. in International Studies from the University of Pennsylvania; and studies Cognitive Psychology from the University of Tel Aviv in Israel.Read Full Background




